Pre-heat your #oven{} to 210 degrees. Scrub (but don't peel) the @sweet potato{2} under some water. Slice them in half lengthways. Slice each half lengthways into three pieces (or four pieces if it's a big 'un). Chop the @cherry tomatoes{2} in half. Break the @garlic bulb{1} into cloves.

Coat the sweet potato and garlic (leave the cloves whole and skin on!) in @olive oil{2%tbsp} and a good pinch of @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Place on a #baking tray{} with the @rosemary{4%sprigs}(leaves scattered over). Put in your oven on the top shelf for ~{25%minutes}.

Mix @olive oil{4%tbsp} with the @chilli flakes{1/2%tsp}, @dried oregano{1%tsp}, a pinch of @salt{} and a few grinds of @black pepper{}. Pour this marinade onto a baking tray big enough to hold the steak and tomatoes.

Heat a #non-stick frying pan{} on your #hob{} until it's super hot. Add in a splash of @olive oil{} and when it's almost smoking, fry the @flank steak{4}. Cook for ~{2%minutes} on each side without touching it in between.

> We like our steak medium, but if you want a more well done steak, cook it for a little longer.

Once cooked, lay the steak in the marinade. Let it marinate for at least ~{3%minutes} on each side. Meanwhile, add all of your cherry tomatoes into the marinade as well, flat-side down.

> Cover your tray with some tin foil to keep the steak warm.

Your potatoes should be done by now, so take them out of your oven.

> Your roasted sweet potatoes should be crispy on the outside and soft in the middle.

Squeeze the garlic cloves from their skin back in with your sweet potato. They should be soft and slightly caramelised.

> If you're not a huge garlic fan, you can leave the garlic out.

Remove your steak from its marinade and slice it into 1cm thick slices on the diagonal.

> Reserve the marinade as you can pour this over the finished dish.

Now it's time to plate up! On each plate, mix the @baby leaves{2} with your marinated cherry tomatoes. Top with your steak slices, and add the roasted sweet potatoes (and garlic, if you like) on the side and get stuck in!